argument.p:
The great corruption of the wicked world;
their prophane and presumptuous speeches;
The preservation of the Church.

He praiseth God for his Spirit and providence;
professeth his hope of resurrection
and life everlasting.

The names and properties of the Scriptures;
the benefit of obeying them, which makes
the godly sue for grace.

div.l:
Thy pray'r
                        •
                      fulfill;

argument.p:
A memoriall of Gods miracles in Aegypt;
They are forced to let Israel go with honour
and riches.

The corporall and spirituall adultery of Israel;
The zeal of Phinehas, their provoking
of Moses to passion, and lenitie to the Canaanites.
